{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777747412039,"sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_MhvsmxzNJy6xxwK9dnek8492","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\n2: title: \"Gshare branch predictor with BTB\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current core has no branch predictor — it always predicts not-taken\n6:   and pays a 2-cycle misprediction penalty on every taken branch (and JAL/JALR).\n7:   CoreMark has ~15-20% conditional branches with ~50-60% taken rate, plus\n8:   frequent JAL calls/returns. A gshare predictor can achieve ~92-95% accuracy\n9:   on CoreMark, eliminating most of the ~0.15-0.20 CPI penalty. This is the\n10:   single highest-ROI microarchitectural feature missing from the baseline.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Add a gshare branch predictor: an N-bit global history register (GHR) XORed\n13:   with PC bits indexes a pattern history table (PHT) of 2-bit saturating\n14:   counters. A small direct-mapped BTB caches target addresses for recently\n15:   taken branches. Prediction occurs in IF stage: if BTB hit and PHT says taken,\n16:   redirect fetch to BTB target. JAL is always predicted taken with immediate\n17:   target. On branch resolution in EX, update GHR, PHT, and BTB; on mispredict,\n18:   flush the pipeline and restore correct PC. Keep area minimal: 64-256 PHT\n19:   entries, 8-16 BTB entries, 6-8 bit GHR. This should improve IPC by 5-12%\n20:   with negligible Fmax impact.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 5\n23:   confidence: medium\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/branch_predictor.sv\n26:     description: \"New module: gshare predictor with GHR, PHT of 2-bit saturating counters, and direct-mapped BTB. Provides predict_taken and predict_target outputs, accepts update signals from EX stage.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Integrate predictor output into fetch PC selection. On predicted taken branch, redirect PC to predict_target instead of pc+4. Maintain speculative state for recovery on mispredict.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"On branch resolution, produce predictor update signals: actual branch direction, actual target, and PC for index computation. Signal mispredict to trigger pipeline flush.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Wire branch_predictor into the pipeline: connect predictor to IF stage, connect EX stage update signals back to predictor, route mispredict flush through hazard unit.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n34:     description: \"Add predictor configuration parameters (GHR width, PHT depth, BTB depth) and any needed struct definitions for predictor interfaces.\"\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\ntitle: \"Gshare branch predictor with BTB\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current core has no branch predictor — it always predicts not-taken\n  and pays a 2-cycle misprediction penalty on every taken branch (and JAL/JALR).\n  CoreMark has ~15-20% conditional branches with ~50-60% taken rate, plus\n  frequent JAL calls/returns. A gshare predictor can achieve ~92-95% accuracy\n  on CoreMark, eliminating most of the ~0.15-0.20 CPI penalty. This is the\n  single highest-ROI microarchitectural feature missing from the baseline.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a gshare branch predictor: an N-bit global history register (GHR) XORed\n  with PC bits indexes a pattern history table (PHT) of 2-bit saturating\n  counters. A small direct-mapped BTB caches target addresses for recently\n  taken branches. Prediction occurs in IF stage: if BTB hit and PHT says taken,\n  redirect fetch to BTB target. JAL is always predicted taken with immediate\n  target. On branch resolution in EX, update GHR, PHT, and BTB; on mispredict,\n  flush the pipeline and restore correct PC. Keep area minimal: 64-256 PHT\n  entries, 8-16 BTB entries, 6-8 bit GHR. This should improve IPC by 5-12%\n  with negligible Fmax impact.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1777747412034,"end":1777747412038}},"id":"prt_dea00bd35001mIxXx5Y5ajZ54i","sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","messageID":"msg_dea00af87001XiJk4iisVBFGnS"}}
