{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777747560196,"sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_H91FipEOxBXkPcaHORSq9685","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-001-r1s0\ntitle: \"Static backward-taken forward-not-taken branch prediction in IF stage\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current core treats every branch as not-taken until EX resolution, paying\n  a full 2-cycle penalty on every taken branch. CoreMark's hot loops are\n  overwhelmingly backward branches (loop-closing BEQ/BNE with negative offset).\n  Adding a zero-state static predictor — predict taken when instr[31]==1 for\n  B-type opcodes — eliminates the 2-cycle bubble for ~85% of taken branches\n  with zero area overhead beyond a sign-bit check and an immediate adder in IF.\n  This is the classic textbook improvement from Patterson & Hennessy that\n  requires no PHT, no BTB, and no training logic — pure combinatorial addition.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend the IF stage to pre-decode the opcode and sign-bit of B-type branches.\n  When instr[6:0] == BRANCH and instr[31] == 1 (negative offset, i.e. backward\n  branch), redirect the PC immediately to PC + B_imm, bypassing the 2-cycle\n  wait for EX-stage branch resolution. The prediction flows through the pipeline\n  as a predicted_taken bit in if_id_t / id_ex_t. EX stage compares actual branch\n  direction against the prediction and fires a redirect only on mispredict\n  (redirecting to PC+4 on false-positive, or to branch_target on false-negative).\n  Correct predictions cost zero cycles; mispredicts pay the existing 2-cycle\n  penalty. No new state elements, no training — the PHT/BTBs are left to future\n  predictor-category hypotheses.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add logic predicted_taken field to if_id_t and id_ex_t packed structs so the branch prediction travels from IF through ID to EX for mispredict detection.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add combinational branch detection (opcode == 7'b1100011) and static prediction (instr[31] == 1 for backward branches). Compute B-type immediate and bypass PC to predict_target on predicted-taken. Pass predicted_taken to if_id_t output.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Copy predicted_taken from the if_id_t input into the id_ex_t register so it reaches the EX stage for mispredict comparison.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Replace unconditional branch redirect with mispredict-based redirect: redirect fires only when branch_taken != predicted_taken (or on jumps). On false-positive mispredict redirect to pc+4. On false-negative mispredict redirect to branch_target.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777747560186,"end":1777747560195}},"id":"prt_dea02bf740011ZwK3mAUgopaD5","sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","messageID":"msg_dea00c608001ZsitIcmTb2TgXA"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1777747560555,"sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","part":{"id":"prt_dea02b39d001FemASWxtxIUTFG","messageID":"msg_dea00c608001ZsitIcmTb2TgXA","sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. The existing gshare predictor hypothesis (hyp-003) is in the `predictor` category. My task is a `micro_opt` — a different, simpler angle. The most impactful single micro-optimization for this 5-stage in-order core is **static backward-taken branch prediction**, which requires no state (unlike a full predictor), just a sign-bit check and immediate computation in IF to eliminate the 2-cycle penalty for loop-back branches. Let me write the hypothesis.","time":{"start":1777747538845,"end":1777747560552}}}
