{"type":"text","timestamp":1777747579162,"sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","part":{"id":"prt_dea034677001pThRPHyxJD3BYD","messageID":"msg_dea0308b5001W0aIe2NI7i5KgE","sessionID":"ses_21606094fffeICSrkiMHKBN4rr","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written. It proposes a **static backward-taken branch predictor** — zero state, pure combinatorial sign-bit check on B-type instructions in IF. This eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for CoreMark's loop-back branches (~85% of taken branches) without the area/complexity of a full predictor. Four files touched, all confined to pipeline refinements consistent with the NRET=2 contract.","time":{"start":1777747576439,"end":1777747579161}}}
