 are nearly always produced by the immediately preceding instruction, so every taken branch triggers the stall and nets zero IPC gain.\n- 2026-05-02 hyp-20260502-003-r1s2 (broken, n/a): Gshare+BTB redirect logic compared predicted-vs-actual next PC on all instructions, not just branches; BTB aliasing on non-branch PCs caused spurious pipeline flushes that riscv-formal's reg and insn_beq checks caught as incorrect retirement.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1777749903265,"end":1777749903277}},"id":"prt_dea26c09f001SY7V5uLEaV2VX1","sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","messageID":"msg_dea23bd62001OHOCHRvZ30mq3a"}}
