{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777749911115,"sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_JmbZdmawNm7JK9pgACrb5745","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"id\": \"baseline-bench-a3930e2\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 301.04, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.21, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9880, \"ff\": 1858, \"seeds\": [121.29, 135.21, 136.07], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-02T18:35:51.802352Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n2: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260502-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"Static backward-taken forward-not-taken branch prediction in IF stage\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current core treats every branch as not-taken until EX resolution, paying\\na full 2-cycle penalty on every taken branch. CoreMark's hot loops are\\noverwhelmingly backward branches (loop-closing BEQ/BNE with negative offset).\\nAdding a zero-state static predictor \\u2014 predict taken when instr[31]==1 for\\nB-type opcodes \\u2014 eliminates the 2-cycle bubble for ~85% of taken branches\\nwith zero area overhead beyond a sign-bit check and an immediate adder in IF.\\nThis is the classic textbook improvement from Patterson & Hennessy that\\nrequires no PHT, no BTB, and no training logic \\u2014 pure combinatorial addition.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current core treats every branch as not-taken until EX resolution, paying\\na full 2-cycle penalty on every taken branch. CoreMark's hot loops are\\noverwhelmingly backward branches (loop-closing BEQ/BNE with negative offset).\\nAdding a zero-state static predictor \\u2014 predict taken when instr[31]==1 for\\nB-type opcodes \\u2014 eliminates the 2-cycle bubble for ~85% of taken branches\\nwith zero area overhead beyond a sign-bit check and an immediate adder in IF.\\nThis is the classic textbook improvement from Patterson & Hennessy that\\nrequires no PHT, no BTB, and no training logic \\u2014 pure combinatorial addition.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the IF stage to pre-decode the opcode and sign-bit of B-type branches.\\nWhen instr[6:0] == BRANCH and instr[31] == 1 (negative offset, i.e. backward\\nbranch), redirect the PC immediately to PC + B_imm, bypassing the 2-cycle\\nwait for EX-stage branch resolution. The prediction flows through the pipeline\\nas a predicted_taken bit in if_id_t / id_ex_t. EX stage compares actual branch\\ndirection against the prediction and fires a redirect only on mispredict\\n(redirecting to PC+4 on false-positive, or to branch_target on false-negati... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260502-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Move branch resolution from EX to ID stage to halve taken-branch penalty\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all branches in the EX stage (stage 3),\\nincurring a full 2-cycle penalty per taken branch. CoreMark is branch-heavy\\n(~12% taken branches), wasting ~12-13% of issue slots on branch flushes.\\nMoving resolution one stage earlier (to ID) cuts this to 1 cycle, reclaiming\\nroughly half those lost slots with no prediction hardware.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all branches in the EX stage (stage 3),\\nincurring a full 2-cycle penalty per taken branch. CoreMark is branch-heavy\\n(~12% taken branches), wasting ~12-13% of issue slots on branch flushes.\\nMoving resolution one stage earlier (to ID) cuts this to 1 cycle, reclaiming\\nroughly half those lost slots with no prediction hardware.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"By adding branch operand forwarding muxes and a comparator to the ID stage,\\nand adding a small new hazard (stall 1 cycle when branch depends on EX-stage\\ninstruction), taken-branch penalty drops from 2 cycles to 1 cycle. The\\ncomparator and forwarding logic removed from the EX stage partially offsets\\nthe added ID-stage logic, keeping the critical path balance intact. Net IPC\\ngain for CoreMark should be ~5-8%.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add branch operand forwarding muxes (2x 3:1, from regfile, EX/MEM, MEM/WB),\\na 6-way branch comparator (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU), branch target adder,\\nand redirect output. Add a new RAW hazard input signal (branch_depends_on_ex)\\nthat defers ID/EX capture when asserted, inserting a 1-cycle bubble so the\\nbranch can forward from EX next cycle.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove branch resolution logic (comparator, branch_cond/taken/target\\ncomputation, branch redirect). Keep JAL/JAL... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n4: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Gshare branch predictor with BTB\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current core has no branch predictor \\u2014 it always predicts not-taken\\nand pays a 2-cycle misprediction penalty on every taken branch (and JAL/JALR).\\nCoreMark has ~15-20% conditional branches with ~50-60% taken rate, plus\\nfrequent JAL calls/returns. A gshare predictor can achieve ~92-95% accuracy\\non CoreMark, eliminating most of the ~0.15-0.20 CPI penalty. This is the\\nsingle highest-ROI microarchitectural feature missing from the baseline.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current core has no branch predictor \\u2014 it always predicts not-taken\\nand pays a 2-cycle misprediction penalty on every taken branch (and JAL/JALR).\\nCoreMark has ~15-20% conditional branches with ~50-60% taken rate, plus\\nfrequent JAL calls/returns. A gshare predictor can achieve ~92-95% accuracy\\non CoreMark, eliminating most of the ~0.15-0.20 CPI penalty. This is the\\nsingle highest-ROI microarchitectural feature missing from the baseline.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a gshare branch predictor: an N-bit global history register (GHR) XORed\\nwith PC bits indexes a pattern history table (PHT) of 2-bit saturating\\ncounters. A small direct-mapped BTB caches target addresses for recently\\ntaken branches. Prediction occurs in IF stage: if BTB hit and PHT says taken,\\nredirect fetch to BTB target. JAL is always predicted taken with immediate\\ntarget. On branch resolution in EX, update GHR, PHT, and BTB; on mispredict,\\nflush the pipeline and restore correct PC. Keep area minimal: 64-256 PHT\\nentries, 8-16 BTB entries, 6-8 bit GHR. This should improve IPC by 5-12%\\nwith negligible Fmax impact.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/branch_predictor.sv\", \"description\": \"New module: gshare predictor with GHR, PHT of 2-bit saturating counters, and direct-mapped BTB. Provides predict_taken and predict_target outputs, acc... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(End of file - total 4 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-a3930e2\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 301.04, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.21, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9880, \"ff\": 1858, \"seeds\": [121.29, 135.21, 136.07], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-02T18:35:51.802352Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20