{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777750011912,"sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_HHyPTLtyR0PsDcVWoMAK3008","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r2s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-001-r2s0\ntitle: \"MEM-to-EX load-use forwarding to eliminate 1-cycle load-use stall\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage pipeline inserts a 1-cycle bubble on every load-use\n  hazard (a LOAD in EX whose destination is read by the next instruction in ID).\n  CoreMark's list-processing and pointer-chasing loops contain tight load-use\n  chains where a loaded address feeds the next load's base register. Every such\n  chain wastes ~1 cycle per load, contributing ~4-6% CPI overhead. Prior attempts\n  all targeted branch prediction (hyp-001 through hyp-003), all of which failed\n  or regressed; no hypothesis has touched the load-use forwarding path yet.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a MEM-stage load-data forwarding path to the EX-stage operand muxes.\n  When the instruction in the MEM stage is a LOAD (ex_mem.ctrl.mem_read=1) and\n  its destination register matches id_ex.rs1 or id_ex.rs2, forward dmem_rdata\n  (the combinational loaded word, available zero-wait on FPGA) directly to the\n  ALU operand instead of stalling. The forward_unit receives ex_mem.ctrl.mem_read\n  as a new input and uses a 2'd3 encoding for this new forwarding source.\n  The hazard_unit suppresses the load-use stall when this forwarding path will\n  resolve the dependency. dmem_rdata is routed from core.sv into ex_stage as\n  a new port. This is a pure combinational addition — no speculation, no new\n  pipeline registers, no RVFI trace disturbance. All three prior branch-prediction\n  hypotheses (hyp-001, hyp-002, hyp-003) failed or regressed, confirming that\n  the non-speculative load-use path is the safer micro-opt vector.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Add ex_mem_mem_read input. When ex_mem.ctrl.mem_read=1 and the LOAD's rd\n      matches id_ex_rs1 or id_ex_rs2, output fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'd3 (MEM_LOAD_DATA)\n      instead of stalling. This new source has higher priority than EX/MEM alu_result\n      (2'd1) because the LOAD data is fresher than the stale address in alu_result.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add dmem_rdata input port. Extend the operand forwarding muxes to handle\n      fwd_sel == 2'd3 by selecting dmem_rdata. The 2'd1 (EX/MEM alu_result) path\n      must be gated for LOAD instructions since ex_mem.alu_result holds the load\n      address, not the loaded data.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Add ex_mem_mem_read input. Suppress the load-use stall (stall_id=0,\n      flush_id=0 for the load-use case) when ex_mem.ctrl.mem_read=1 because the\n      forward_unit will resolve the dependency via dmem_rdata forwarding. The\n      original load-use stall logic only fires when the producer in EX/MEM is NOT\n      a load (i.e., it's an ALU op whose result won't be available until WB).\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Route io_dmemRData into the ex_stage and forward_unit instances as new\n      input ports (dmem_rdata). Also route ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read into both\n      hazard_unit and forward_unit. No top-level IO changes.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r2s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777750011902,"end":1777750011911}},"id":"prt_dea2801db001xhMFjyxTA1o7BE","sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","messageID":"msg_dea27e56c00132FNAFxVATZDO9"}}
