{"type":"text","timestamp":1777750043528,"sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","part":{"id":"prt_dea28d626001y4bfouaX2JmyeB","messageID":"msg_dea28cd81001zeiZpshf9dJeKm","sessionID":"ses_215dc42d9ffeBdy0cqVRfweyKm","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written and validated at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r2s0.yaml`.\n\n**Proposal**: MEM-to-EX load-use forwarding — eliminates the 1-cycle stall when a LOAD's result is consumed by the next instruction. Adds a `2'd3` forwarding source in `forward_unit` that routes `dmem_rdata` (combinational, zero-wait on FPGA) directly to the EX-stage operand mux. The `hazard_unit` suppresses the load-use stall when this forwarding path resolves the dependency. Touches 4 files: `forward_unit.sv`, `ex_stage.sv`, `hazard_unit.sv`, `core.sv`.\n\nThis is the first hypothesis targeting the load-use path (all three prior attempts targeted branch prediction and failed or regressed).","time":{"start":1777750038054,"end":1777750043526}}}
