{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777747755076,"sessionID":"ses_216060a9cffexhkFr5DZTait0t","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_mK2aEh5iLy9uzSQPJ2SK5144","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-002-r1s1\ntitle: \"Move branch resolution from EX to ID stage to halve taken-branch penalty\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all branches in the EX stage (stage 3),\n  incurring a full 2-cycle penalty per taken branch. CoreMark is branch-heavy\n  (~12% taken branches), wasting ~12-13% of issue slots on branch flushes.\n  Moving resolution one stage earlier (to ID) cuts this to 1 cycle, reclaiming\n  roughly half those lost slots with no prediction hardware.\nhypothesis: |\n  By adding branch operand forwarding muxes and a comparator to the ID stage,\n  and adding a small new hazard (stall 1 cycle when branch depends on EX-stage\n  instruction), taken-branch penalty drops from 2 cycles to 1 cycle. The\n  comparator and forwarding logic removed from the EX stage partially offsets\n  the added ID-stage logic, keeping the critical path balance intact. Net IPC\n  gain for CoreMark should be ~5-8%.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add branch operand forwarding muxes (2x 3:1, from regfile, EX/MEM, MEM/WB),\n      a 6-way branch comparator (BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU), branch target adder,\n      and redirect output. Add a new RAW hazard input signal (branch_depends_on_ex)\n      that defers ID/EX capture when asserted, inserting a 1-cycle bubble so the\n      branch can forward from EX next cycle.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Remove branch resolution logic (comparator, branch_cond/taken/target\n      computation, branch redirect). Keep JAL/JALR resolution and ALU operand\n      forwarding intact.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Route fwd_ex_mem and fwd_mem_wb values to ID stage for branch forwarding.\n      Route ex_mem_rd/mem_wb_rd and their reg_write bits to the new ID-side\n      forwarding logic. Pipe the ID-stage redirect to both if_stage and\n      hazard_unit, OR-ing it with the remaining EX redirect for JAL/JALR.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Add new hazard: branch_in_id consumes rd produced by instruction currently\n      in EX stage. When detected, assert stall_if=1 and stall_id=1 so the branch\n      holds in ID for one cycle, then forwards from EX/MEM. Takes lower priority\n      than dmem_stall to preserve the existing stall precedence.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1.yaml","time":{"start":1777747755066,"end":1777747755075}},"id":"prt_dea05af360017mS5m5ks63wdcs","sessionID":"ses_216060a9cffexhkFr5DZTait0t","messageID":"msg_dea0564ce0017MKtn1Hl5jt3hz"}}
