{"type":"text","timestamp":1777747790379,"sessionID":"ses_216060a9cffexhkFr5DZTait0t","part":{"id":"prt_dea067c5b002NdoKAnPrlh6K07","messageID":"msg_dea0673d3001vNlOKCWlmxW15m","sessionID":"ses_216060a9cffexhkFr5DZTait0t","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis `hyp-20260502-002-r1s1` written and validated.\n\n**Summary**: Move branch resolution from EX to ID stage — a structural pipeline optimization that halves the taken-branch penalty from 2 cycles to 1. The ID stage gains forwarding muxes and a comparator; EX sheds its branch logic, keeping the critical path roughly balanced. A new mini-hazard stalls the branch for 1 cycle when it depends on the instruction currently in EX. Expected IPC gain ~5% with minimal Fmax impact.","time":{"start":1777747786843,"end":1777747790378}}}
