{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777749939760,"sessionID":"ses_215dc43d0ffeTSFoJdpYte7q4z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_n4MkONwh2mx6WsWaxd9z4368","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r2s1.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-002-r2s1\ntitle: \"Dual-issue in-order superscalar pipeline with static pairing\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline single-issue pipeline retires at most 1 instruction per cycle,\n  capping IPC at 1.0. CoreMark contains significant instruction-level\n  parallelism — independent ALU chains, loads whose results feed unrelated\n  downstream ops, and branch/compare pairs. A 2-way in-order superscalar\n  design can exploit this slack without speculation. The NRET=2 RVFI contract\n  is already wired into the core, formal harness, cosim, and FPGA bench, so\n  the retirement infrastructure for dual-issue already exists and has been\n  validated end-to-end. Prior structural attempts targeted branch latency\n  reduction (moving resolution from EX to ID), which failed because CoreMark\n  branch operands are nearly always produced by the immediately preceding\n  instruction. Dual-issue avoids this dependency bottleneck by issuing two\n  independent instructions simultaneously rather than trying to accelerate\n  dependent chains.\nhypothesis: |\n  Widen the pipeline to a 2-way in-order superscalar: fetch pairs of 32-bit\n  instructions from imem (buffered through a single-cycle prefetch latch since\n  imem is 32-bit wide), decode both in parallel, check for intra-pair data\n  hazards and structural conflicts (at most one memory op, at most one branch,\n  at most one M-extension op per pair), issue 0/1/2 instructions per cycle.\n  Add a second simple ALU (integer ops only, no M-extension) for the second\n  pipe. Extend forwarding to cover intra-pair dependencies (pair-forwarding:\n  first instruction's result feeds second instruction's operand in the same\n  cycle). Both instructions in a pair retire atomically on the same cycle with\n  the older on channel 0 and the younger on channel 1. On single-issue cycles,\n  retirement follows the existing channel-0-only convention. Introduce static\n  pairing heuristics at decode time — prefer ALU+ALU, ALU+branch, or\n  load+independent-ALU pairings — and fall back to single-issue when no valid\n  pair exists or a hazard is detected. This should increase CoreMark IPC from\n  ~0.85 to ~1.05-1.15, yielding a net fitness improvement of 20-30% after\n  accounting for a modest Fmax regression from the wider datapath.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 20\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Rewire top-level for dual-issue: instantiate dual decode, dual ALU pipes, merge dual results into single MEM stage, drive both RVFI channels with paired retirement.\"\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add dual-issue bundle types (pair id_ex_pair_t carrying two id_ex_t payloads plus valid bits), widen control-path signals to carry two-issue information.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add a single-instruction prefetch latch to accumulate instruction pairs across two imem fetches; emit pair to ID stage when two valid instructions are available.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Dual decode: instantiate two decoders in parallel, check intra-pair RAW/WAR/WAW hazards and structural conflicts, determine issue count, generate two control bundles.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add second ALU (simple integer only, no M-extension) for pipe B; implement intra-pair forwarding from pipe-A ALU result to pipe-B operand inputs; route results into dual ex_mem payload.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Extend hazard detection for dual-issue: load-use on either pipe, inter-pair RAW hazards between successive dual-issue groups, dmem structural hazard (at most one memory op per cycle), M-unit structural hazard.\"\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: \"Add forwarding sources for the second ALU pipe results in EX/MEM and MEM/WB; handle the case where both pipes produce results that subsequent instructions may need.\"\n  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n    description: \"Add a second synchronous write port so both instructions in a dual-issue pair can write back in the same cycle; maintain write-first bypass semantics on both ports.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r2s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r2s1.yaml","time":{"start":1777749939750,"end":1777749939759}},"id":"prt_dea26e91b001CTapCDXE2U3V4b","sessionID":"ses_215dc43d0ffeTSFoJdpYte7q4z","messageID":"msg_dea26df0a001ruH4Z9wzNDkjdR"}}
