{"type":"text","timestamp":1777749966404,"sessionID":"ses_215dc43d0ffeTSFoJdpYte7q4z","part":{"id":"prt_dea27ace8001EI6C4zFJcK5K39","messageID":"msg_dea2792ba001A8dXyUzPHjLx3W","sessionID":"ses_215dc43d0ffeTSFoJdpYte7q4z","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written and validated at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r2s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Dual-issue in-order superscalar pipeline — the first structural hypothesis to target IPC directly (rather than branch latency). Prior structural attempts (moving branch resolution from EX to ID) failed because they chased dependent-chain acceleration; this hypothesis instead exploits independent instruction pairs. The NRET=2 RVFI contract is already wired end-to-end, so the retirement side needs no contract changes. Conservative static pairing rules (at most one memory op, one branch, one M-op per pair) keep the implementation tractable for formal verification.","time":{"start":1777749961961,"end":1777749966402}}}
