{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777747220695,"sessionID":"ses_2160609d6ffeKHNoQWjRqR0FjP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_BTi4q5F9KF5TdLUjGbg18486","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\ntitle: \"Gshare branch predictor with BTB\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current core has no branch predictor — it always predicts not-taken\n  and pays a 2-cycle misprediction penalty on every taken branch (and JAL/JALR).\n  CoreMark has ~15-20% conditional branches with ~50-60% taken rate, plus\n  frequent JAL calls/returns. A gshare predictor can achieve ~92-95% accuracy\n  on CoreMark, eliminating most of the ~0.15-0.20 CPI penalty. This is the\n  single highest-ROI microarchitectural feature missing from the baseline.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a gshare branch predictor: an N-bit global history register (GHR) XORed\n  with PC bits indexes a pattern history table (PHT) of 2-bit saturating\n  counters. A small direct-mapped BTB caches target addresses for recently\n  taken branches. Prediction occurs in IF stage: if BTB hit and PHT says taken,\n  redirect fetch to BTB target. JAL is always predicted taken with immediate\n  target. On branch resolution in EX, update GHR, PHT, and BTB; on mispredict,\n  flush the pipeline and restore correct PC. Keep area minimal: 64-256 PHT\n  entries, 8-16 BTB entries, 6-8 bit GHR. This should improve IPC by 5-12%\n  with negligible Fmax impact.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/branch_predictor.sv\n    description: \"New module: gshare predictor with GHR, PHT of 2-bit saturating counters, and direct-mapped BTB. Provides predict_taken and predict_target outputs, accepts update signals from EX stage.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Integrate predictor output into fetch PC selection. On predicted taken branch, redirect PC to predict_target instead of pc+4. Maintain speculative state for recovery on mispredict.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"On branch resolution, produce predictor update signals: actual branch direction, actual target, and PC for index computation. Signal mispredict to trigger pipeline flush.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire branch_predictor into the pipeline: connect predictor to IF stage, connect EX stage update signals back to predictor, route mispredict flush through hazard unit.\"\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add predictor configuration parameters (GHR width, PHT depth, BTB depth) and any needed struct definitions for predictor interfaces.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1777747220685,"end":1777747220694}},"id":"prt_de9fd85ec001RmhqutVBGKwH8N","sessionID":"ses_2160609d6ffeKHNoQWjRqR0FjP","messageID":"msg_de9fd5315001Amb4Wm45E3CE5P"}}
