 are nearly always produced by the immediately preceding instruction, so every taken branch triggers the stall and nets zero IPC gain.\n- 2026-05-02 hyp-20260502-003-r1s2 (broken, n/a): Gshare+BTB redirect logic compared predicted-vs-actual next PC on all instructions, not just branches; BTB aliasing on non-branch PCs caused spurious pipeline flushes that riscv-formal's reg and insn_beq checks caught as incorrect retirement.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1777749842449,"end":1777749842455}},"id":"prt_dea25d3ca00197Ib7bFC3AyR7C","sessionID":"ses_215dc4340ffeHsZffOxnKvi5TS","messageID":"msg_dea25bf37001w6yftSlduP1Qo2"}}
