{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777750006897,"sessionID":"ses_215dc4340ffeHsZffOxnKvi5TS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_4PxNcllzJz3ZzOP481Qy8715","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r2s2.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-003-r2s2\ntitle: \"Bimodal branch predictor with BTB redirecting from ID stage\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline core always predicts not-taken, paying a 2-cycle penalty on\n  every taken branch (~65% of branches, ~20% instruction mix). Prior Gshare\n  attempt (r1s2) failed because it compared predicted-vs-actual PC on ALL\n  instructions, causing BTB aliasing on non-branch PCs to trigger spurious\n  flushes. Prior ID-resolution attempt (r1s1) failed because CoreMark branch\n  operands depend on the immediately preceding instruction, making data-\n  dependent stalls cancel the benefit. This design predicts (not resolves)\n  in ID — no operand dependency — and only predicts on instructions the\n  decoder confirms are branches, avoiding the Gshare aliasing bug.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a bimodal branch predictor (64-entry PHT of 2-bit saturating counters\n  indexed by PC[7:2]) and a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB. In ID stage, when\n  the decoder identifies a conditional branch, probe both tables. If PHT\n  MSB is 1 (predict taken) and BTB hits, assert a predict_redirect to IF\n  stage that updates PC to BTB target and flushes the single wrong-path IF\n  instruction. The branch instruction proceeds to EX for validation; the\n  predict_redirect does NOT flush ID/EX. In EX, compare predicted vs actual\n  outcome: on match, update PHT counter normally; on mispredict, correct\n  pc_next in the pipeline register (so RVFI pc_wdata/pc_fwd stays consistent),\n  assert a resolve_redirect to refetch from the correct target, and update\n  PHT. BTB is filled on taken branches at EX resolution time. Non-branch\n  instructions NEVER trigger prediction (critical difference from r1s2).\n  JAL/JALR are unconditional and not predicted by this unit. RVFI PC values\n  come from pipeline registers carrying commit-time (non-speculative) PCs;\n  mispredict correction of pc_next in EX ensures the pc_fwd formal invariant\n  holds regardless of prediction accuracy.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/branch_predictor.sv\n    description: \"New module: bimodal branch predictor with 64-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT (indexed by PC[7:2]) and 16-entry direct-mapped BTB ({tag, target, valid}). Combinational lookup: predict_taken = PHT[PC[7:2]][1] && BTB_hit; predict_target = BTB target. Update interface: train_taken/train_not_taken on resolved branches; btb_write on taken branches to cache target address.\"\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add predicted_taken field to id_ex_t and ex_mem_t bundles for carrying prediction state through the pipeline to EX-stage validation. Add predictor training interface signals.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Integrate branch predictor: on decoded conditional branch, probe predictor for direction + target. If predicted taken with BTB hit, emit predict_redirect and predict_target outputs to redirect IF stage PC. Store predicted_taken bit in ID/EX register for EX-stage validation. Non-branch instructions must not trigger prediction lookup.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add misprediction detection: compare predicted_taken from id_ex_t against actual branch_taken computed in EX. On mispredict: override pc_next in ex_mem_t to the actual (not predicted) next PC (correcting RVFI pc_wdata), assert resolve_redirect to IF stage to refetch correct path, and drive predictor train interface (update PHT counter direction + BTB write on taken). On correct prediction: train PHT normally, no redirect needed.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Accept predict_redirect and predict_target from ID stage as separate inputs (distinct from EX resolve_redirect). Predict redirect updates PC and flushes the current IF instruction (which is the wrong-path instruction after the predicted branch) but does NOT trigger id_stage flush (the branch must proceed to EX for validation).\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Instantiate branch_predictor module. Wire predict_redirect/predict_target from id_stage to if_stage. Keep EX resolve_redirect separate (feeds hazard_unit for full pipeline flush on branch resolution). Wire predictor train interface from ex_stage to branch_predictor. All RVFI PC fields (pc_rdata, pc_wdata) are driven from mem_wb_w pipeline register values, never from speculative fetch addresses.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Add predict_redirect input from ID stage. On predict_redirect: assert stall_if=0 (PC will update), flush_if=1 (kill wrong-path IF instruction), but explicitly do NOT assert flush_id or stall_id (the branch in ID/EX must survive for EX-stage validation). Resolve_redirect from EX retains existing full-pipeline-flush behavior.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r2s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r2s2.yaml","time":{"start":1777750006887,"end":1777750006896}},"id":"prt_dea27cce8001mskBqmhFgj27fo","sessionID":"ses_215dc4340ffeHsZffOxnKvi5TS","messageID":"msg_dea2615bd001NVg2ElmM9deNdx"}}
