{"type":"text","timestamp":1777750040603,"sessionID":"ses_215dc4340ffeHsZffOxnKvi5TS","part":{"id":"prt_dea28c444001H9wbZKar2Q2wmZ","messageID":"msg_dea28b780001p9RYJdT1V7sgp0","sessionID":"ses_215dc4340ffeHsZffOxnKvi5TS","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis `hyp-20260502-003-r2s2` written and validated. It proposes a **bimodal branch predictor with BTB redirecting from ID stage**, specifically addressing the three prior failures:\n\n- **vs r1s0 (static IF prediction)**: Predicts in ID, not IF — RVFI PCs come from pipeline registers, never speculative fetch. Mispredict correction of `pc_next` in EX preserves the `pc_fwd` invariant.\n- **vs r1s1 (ID resolution)**: Predicts (no operands needed), not resolves — avoids the data-dependent stall that nullified the IPC gain.\n- **vs r1s2 (Gshare+BTB)**: Only predicts on decoder-confirmed branch instructions — the Gshare bug of comparing predicted-vs-actual on non-branch PCs is eliminated.\n\n7 files changed: new `branch_predictor.sv` + modifications to `core_pkg.sv`, `id_stage.sv`, `ex_stage.sv`, `if_stage.sv`, `core.sv`, `hazard_unit.sv`.","time":{"start":1777750033476,"end":1777750040600}}}
